{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013burAMu51dZqmenaev8tek","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Specification: 205 Real Wallet Integration\n     2→\n     3→## Meta\n     4→\n     5→| Field | Value |\n     6→|-------|-------|\n     7→| Status | Ready |\n     8→| Priority | P0 |\n     9→| Phase | 1 |\n    10→| NR_OF_TRIES | 5 |\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→## Overview\n    15→\n    16→Replace the MockWalletProvider with a real Solana wallet adapter so players can connect browser wallets (Phantom, Solflare, Backpack) and sign real transactions. This is the critical link between the existing UI and the deployed on-chain programs. The visual design and UX flow must remain identical — only the wallet backend changes.\n    17→\n    18→## User Stories\n    19→\n    20→- As a player, I want to connect my Phantom/Solflare wallet so that I can play with real SOL.\n    21→- As a player, I want to see my real on-chain SOL balance so that I know how much I can wager.\n    22→- As a player, I want to sign transactions to create, join, cancel, or claim coinflip matches so that my actions settle on-chain.\n    23→- As a developer, I want a TestWalletProvider that signs real transactions with a test keypair so that E2E tests work without a browser extension.\n    24→\n    25→---\n    26→\n    27→## Scope Alignment\n    28→\n    29→- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 (V1 In Scope: Wallet connection), Section 8 (Phase 1 - Coinflip End-to-End)\n    30→- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n    31→- **Phase boundary**: Phase 1 — required to make coinflip functional\n    32→\n    33→## Implementation Context\n    34→\n    35→**Library Choice: Unified Wallet Kit (`@jup-ag/wallet-adapter`)**\n    36→\n    37→- Package: `@jup-ag/wallet-adapter` (built on `@solana/wallet-adapter-react`)\n    38→- Provides: `UnifiedWalletProvider`, `UnifiedWalletButton`, `useUnifiedWallet`\n    39→- Built-in modal UI with dark theme, multi-language, mobile support\n    40→- Auto-detects Wallet Standard wallets (Phantom, Solflare, Backpack) — no manual adapter list needed\n    41→- Wraps Anza's `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` internally → `useWallet()` hook works from either\n    42→- Why not bare adapter: Unified gives us styled modal + button out of box, no custom UI work\n    43→- Why not ConnectorKit: Different API shape (`useConnector`/`useAccount`), would need adapter layer\n    44→\n    45→**Provider Setup Pattern:**\n    46→\n    47→```tsx\n    48→<ConnectionProvider endpoint={rpcUrl}>\n    49→  <UnifiedWalletProvider wallets={[]} config={{\n    50→    autoConnect: true,\n    51→    env: 'devnet',\n    52→    metadata: { name: 'RNG Utopia', ... },\n    53→    theme: 'dark',\n    54→  }}>\n    55→    <App />\n    56→  </UnifiedWalletProvider>\n    57→</ConnectionProvider>\n    58→```\n    59→\n    60→**Key Codebase Findings:**\n    61→\n    62→- `packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx` — currently wraps `MockWalletProvider`, swap target\n    63→- `packages/wallet/src/types.ts` — `WalletContextValue` interface maps 1:1 to adapter's `useWallet`\n    64→- `packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts` — consumers import from here, bridge to adapter\n    65→- `CoinflipContext.tsx:22` — imports `useWallet` from `@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks`\n    66→- `CoinflipContext.tsx:25-26` — reads `VITE_RPC_URL`, defaults to localhost\n    67→- `chain.ts` — all tx builders use `@solana/web3.js`, no adapter dependency (clean separation)\n    68→- `.env.example` has `VITE_SOLANA_RPC_URL` but code reads `VITE_RPC_URL` (mismatch to fix)\n    69→- `apps/platform/package.json` already depends on `@rng-utopia/wallet: workspace:*`\n    70→\n    71→## Required Context Files\n    72→\n    73→- `packages/wallet/src/` — current MockWalletProvider, useWallet, useBalance, types\n    74→- `packages/wallet/src/mock/MockWalletProvider.tsx` — current mock implementation to preserve\n    75→- `packages/wallet/src/context.ts` — shared WalletContext definition\n    76→- `packages/wallet/src/mock/MockWalletState.ts` — mock state management\n    77→- `apps/platform/src/main.tsx` — entry point wrapping App in MockWalletProvider\n    78→- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` — transaction builders (already use @solana/web3.js)\n    79→- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` — calls chain.ts + wallet sendTransaction\n    80→- `apps/platform/src/App.tsx` — wallet icon, balance display, connected state\n    81→- `apps/platform/.env.example` — env var template (has RPC URL mismatch to fix)\n    82→\n    83→## Contract Files\n    84→\n    85→- `packages/wallet/src/types.ts` — WalletContextValue interface (connect, disconnect, sendTransaction, signMessage, publicKey, connected)\n    86→- `packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts` — hook consumers must not change\n    87→- `packages/wallet/src/useBalance.ts` — balance hook consumers must not change\n    88→- `packages/ui/src/WalletButton.tsx` — UI component consuming wallet hook\n    89→\n    90→---\n    91→\n    92→## Functional Requirements\n    93→\n    94→### FR-1: Real Wallet Connection\n    95→\n    96→Replace MockWalletProvider with Unified Wallet Kit (`@jup-ag/wallet-adapter`). The kit wraps `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` and provides a themed modal + connect button out of the box. Pass `wallets: []` to use Wallet Standard auto-detection — no manual adapter instantiation needed.\n    97→\n    98→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    99→- [ ] Player can connect Phantom, Solflare, or Backpack via the existing wallet UI\n   100→- [ ] Player can disconnect and reconnect without page reload\n   101→- [ ] Wallet connection state persists across page navigation (SPA)\n   102→- [ ] The `useWallet()` hook returns the same shape (connected, connecting, address, publicKey, connect, disconnect, sendTransaction, signMessage)\n   103→- [ ] No wallet-adapter UI chrome leaks into the medieval theme (Unified Wallet Kit's `theme: 'dark'` used, styled to match)\n   104→\n   105→### FR-2: Real Balance Display\n   106→\n   107→Show the player's actual on-chain SOL balance instead of a mock value.\n   108→\n   109→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   110→- [ ] Balance displayed matches the connected wallet's on-chain lamport balance\n   111→- [ ] Balance updates after transactions (create match, join, claim, cancel)\n   112→- [ ] Balance polls or subscribes at a reasonable interval (no stale values after 10s)\n   113→- [ ] `useBalance()` hook returns the same shape (balance, formatted, formattedCompact, loading, error, refresh)\n   114→\n   115→### FR-3: Real Transaction Signing\n   116→\n   117→All coinflip actions must sign and send real transactions via the connected wallet.\n   118→\n   119→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   120→- [ ] Create match builds a transaction via chain.ts and sends it through wallet adapter's sendTransaction\n   121→- [ ] Join match, cancel match, and claim payout work the same way\n   122→- [ ] Transaction confirmation is awaited before updating UI state\n   123→- [ ] Wallet rejection (user clicks \"Cancel\" in Phantom) surfaces a user-friendly error, not a raw exception\n   124→- [ ] RPC errors (insufficient balance, account not found) surface user-friendly messages\n   125→\n   126→### FR-4: RPC Configuration\n   127→\n   128→The app must connect to a configurable Solana RPC endpoint. Note: `.env.example` currently uses `VITE_SOLANA_RPC_URL` but code reads `VITE_RPC_URL` — this mismatch must be resolved (standardize on `VITE_RPC_URL`). The `ConnectionProvider` from `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` wraps the app, making `useConnection()` available to all components (replacing the per-context `Connection` instantiation in `CoinflipContext`).\n   129→\n   130→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   131→- [ ] RPC URL is read from VITE_RPC_URL environment variable\n   132→- [ ] Defaults to devnet when no variable is set\n   133→- [ ] Localhost (test-validator) works when VITE_RPC_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8899\n   134→- [ ] `.env.example` updated to use `VITE_RPC_URL` (fixing mismatch)\n   135→\n   136→### FR-5: TestWalletProvider for CI\n   137→\n   138→A test-only wallet provider that injects a Keypair and signs real transactions without a browser extension.\n   139→\n   140→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   141→- [ ] TestWalletProvider accepts a Keypair and RPC URL\n   142→- [ ] It implements the same WalletContextValue interface as the real provider\n   143→- [ ] It can sign and send transactions to a local test-validator\n   144→- [ ] MockWalletProvider is preserved for visual-only testing (no chain dependency)\n   145→\n   146→### FR-6: Visual Preservation\n   147→\n   148→The wallet swap must not alter the site's visual appearance.\n   149→\n   150→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   151→- [ ] Wallet icon in bottom-right corner remains identical\n   152→- [ ] Balance display format unchanged\n   153→- [ ] Connect/disconnect flow uses the same UI elements (no wallet-adapter default modal unless styled)\n   154→- [ ] All non-wallet pages render identically before and after the swap\n   155→- [ ] Visual regression screenshots (spec 200) pass with zero diff on non-wallet elements\n   156→\n   157→---\n   158→\n   159→## Success Criteria\n   160→\n   161→- A player can connect a real wallet, create a coinflip match, and see it on-chain\n   162→- The site looks identical before and after the wallet swap (verified by visual regression)\n   163→- E2E tests can run with TestWalletProvider against a local validator\n   164→- MockWalletProvider still works for visual/component testing (no chain needed)\n   165→\n   166→---\n   167→\n   168→## Dependencies\n   169→\n   170→- Spec 200 (Visual Regression) — baselines must be captured BEFORE this work begins\n   171→- On-chain programs deployed to localnet or devnet\n   172→- `@jup-ag/wallet-adapter` package (Unified Wallet Kit)\n   173→- `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (peer dependency, provided by Unified Wallet Kit)\n   174→\n   175→## Assumptions\n   176→\n   177→- Unified Wallet Kit (`@jup-ag/wallet-adapter`) chosen per team decision\n   178→- Players use standard Solana browser extension wallets (Phantom, Solflare, Backpack)\n   179→- Privy/embedded wallets are deferred to V1.5 (per DECISIONS.md)\n   180→- The `useWallet()` and `useBalance()` hook interfaces are stable and sufficient\n   181→- Dark theme used (`theme: 'dark'`), can be styled further post-V1\n   182→- Wallet Standard auto-detection means no manual adapter instantiation needed\n   183→\n   184→---\n   185→\n   186→## Validation Plan\n   187→\n   188→| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   189→|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   190→| 1 | Phantom connects | Manual test with Phantom extension | Screenshot of connected state |\n   191→| 2 | Balance is real | Compare displayed balance with `solana balance` CLI | Side-by-side screenshot |\n   192→| 3 | Create match works | Create match, verify PDA exists on-chain | Explorer link or `solana account` output |\n   193→| 4 | Visual unchanged | Spec 200 screenshot diff | Zero-diff report on non-wallet elements |\n   194→| 5 | TestWalletProvider works | E2E test with test-validator | Test pass output |\n   195→| 6 | Hook shape preserved | TypeScript compilation | No type errors in consuming code |\n   196→\n   197→---\n   198→\n   199→## Completion Signal\n   200→\n   201→### Implementation Checklist\n   202→\n   203→#### Pre-existing scaffold (untested — validation required in later iterations)\n   204→- [x] [frontend] `RealWalletProvider.tsx` wrapping `UnifiedWalletProvider` + `ConnectionProvider` + `WalletBridge` mapping adapter hooks to `WalletContextValue` (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n   205→- [x] [frontend] `TestWalletProvider.tsx` accepting `Keypair` + `rpcUrl`, signing real transactions via `sendAndConfirmTransaction` (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n   206→- [x] [frontend] `WalletProvider.tsx` delegates to `MockWalletProvider` or lazy-loaded `RealWalletProvider` based on `VITE_MOCK_MODE` (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n   207→- [x] [frontend] `useBalance.ts` checks `isMock` flag — mock mode reads from `getBalanceLamports()`, real mode polls `connection.getBalance()` every 10s (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n   208→- [x] [frontend] RPG wallet icon in `App.tsx` calls `connect()`/`disconnect()` — `WalletBridge.connect()` opens Unified Wallet modal via `setShowModal(true)` (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n   209→- [x] [frontend] `parseTransactionError()` in `CoinflipContext.tsx` handles: wallet rejection, insufficient funds, network errors, program errors, generic fallback (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n   210→- [x] [frontend] `.env.example` has `VITE_MOCK_MODE`, `VITE_RPC_URL`, `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK` (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n   211→- [x] [frontend] `chain.ts` transaction builders (`buildCreateMatchTx`, `buildJoinMatchTx`, `buildCancelMatchTx`, `buildClaimPayoutTx`) integrated into `CoinflipContext` via `sendTransaction` from `useWallet()` (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n   212→\n   213→#### Iteration 1: Build validation in real wallet mode\n   214→- [x] [frontend] Set `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false`, run `pnpm build` for the platform app — fix any TS compilation errors in `packages/wallet/src/real/`, `packages/wallet/src/test/`, and `packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx`. Run `pnpm lint` (zero errors) and platform `pnpm typecheck` (zero errors). (done: iteration 1)\n   215→\n   216→#### Iteration 2: Shared ConnectionProvider across all wallet modes\n   217→- [x] [frontend] Move `ConnectionProvider` from inside `RealWalletProvider.tsx` to `WalletProvider.tsx` level — wraps both Mock and Real providers. Endpoint: `VITE_RPC_URL` env var, defaults to `https://api.devnet.solana.com`. `RealWalletProvider` drops its own `ConnectionProvider` wrapper and uses the shared one. Verify build + typecheck pass in both mock and real modes. (done: iteration 2)\n   218→\n   219→#### Iteration 3: CoinflipContext + useBalance use shared Connection\n   220→- [x] [frontend] Update `CoinflipContext.tsx` to use `useConnection()` from `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` instead of `new Connection(RPC_URL)` — delete the `RPC_URL` constant and the `useMemo(() => new Connection(...))`. Update `useBalance.ts` to use `useConnection()` instead of its internal `connectionRef` + `getRpcUrl()` — remove the `getConnection` callback, `connectionRef`, and `DEFAULT_RPC_URL` constant. Verify build + typecheck pass. (done: iteration 3)\n   221→\n   222→#### Iteration 4: Mock mode + visual regression preservation\n   223→- [x] [test] Run `pnpm test:visual` — all 17 visual regression baselines pass with zero diff (confirms wallet refactor didn't alter mock mode UI). Start dev server in mock mode (default `VITE_MOCK_MODE` unset), load in Playwright headless, verify zero JS console errors. (done: iteration 4)\n   224→\n   225→#### Iteration 5: Real mode app startup validation\n   226→- [x] [test] Start dev server with `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false` and `VITE_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com`. Load the app in Playwright headless — verify: no JS console errors, wallet icon renders in disconnected state, clicking the wallet icon calls `connect()` without crashing (Unified Wallet modal opens or shows \"no wallets detected\" — both valid in headless). (done: iteration 5)\n   227→\n   228→#### Iteration 6: TestWalletProvider unit test\n   229→- [ ] [test] Write a vitest test in `packages/wallet/src/test/TestWalletProvider.test.tsx`: render a component tree wrapped in `TestWalletProvider({ keypair: Keypair.generate(), rpcUrl: \"https://api.devnet.solana.com\" })`, verify `useWallet()` returns `connected: true` and `publicKey` matching the keypair after mount (use `waitFor`). Also render with `MockWalletProvider` and verify it returns `connected: false` initially. Both tests must pass.\n   230→\n   231→#### Iteration 7: Final verification\n   232→- [ ] [test] Run `pnpm test:visual` — all baselines pass. Run `pnpm lint` and platform `typecheck` — zero errors. Verify app starts in both mock and real modes without console errors. Run `./scripts/verify` — passes (exit 0).\n   233→\n   234→### Testing Requirements\n   235→\n   236→The agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n   237→\n   238→#### Code Quality\n   239→- [ ] All existing tests pass\n   240→- [ ] No lint errors\n   241→- [ ] TypeScript compiles with no errors\n   242→\n   243→#### Functional Verification\n   244→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n   245→- [ ] Wallet connect/disconnect works (validated in Playwright headless — real mode loads, connect() callable)\n   246→- [ ] Transaction building compiles and wallet adapter sendTransaction is callable (TypeScript verification)\n   247→- [ ] Full coinflip lifecycle (create → join → resolve → claim) deferred to 001-coinflip spec (requires VRF oracle)\n   248→\n   249→#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n   250→- [ ] Wallet UI matches existing design (RPG wallet icon preserved)\n   251→- [ ] No wallet-adapter default styling visible on non-wallet pages\n   252→- [ ] Visual regression baselines pass with zero diff in mock mode\n   253→\n   254→#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n   255→- [ ] No JS console errors in mock mode\n   256→- [ ] No JS console errors in real mode (connected to devnet)\n   257→- [ ] No failed RPC requests when connected to valid endpoint\n   258→\n   259→### Iteration Instructions\n   260→\n   261→If ANY check fails:\n   262→1. Identify the specific issue\n   263→2. Fix the code\n   264→3. Re-run tests\n   265→4. Re-verify all criteria\n   266→5. Check again\n   267→\n   268→**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n   269→\n   270→### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n   271→\n   272→After the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n   273→`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n   274→1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n   275→2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n   276→3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n   277→4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n   278→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e148c6ae-d46e-4f5a-b974-9f3c7b2cbc1a","uuid":"5f9f3dab-78f8-4f71-aaf0-8fe7466ac537","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/205-real-wallet/spec.md","content":"# Specification: 205 Real Wallet Integration\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Ready |\n| Priority | P0 |\n| Phase | 1 |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 5 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nReplace the MockWalletProvider with a real Solana wallet adapter so players can connect browser wallets (Phantom, Solflare, Backpack) and sign real transactions. This is the critical link between the existing UI and the deployed on-chain programs. The visual design and UX flow must remain identical — only the wallet backend changes.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a player, I want to connect my Phantom/Solflare wallet so that I can play with real SOL.\n- As a player, I want to see my real on-chain SOL balance so that I know how much I can wager.\n- As a player, I want to sign transactions to create, join, cancel, or claim coinflip matches so that my actions settle on-chain.\n- As a developer, I want a TestWalletProvider that signs real transactions with a test keypair so that E2E tests work without a browser extension.\n\n---\n\n## Scope Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 (V1 In Scope: Wallet connection), Section 8 (Phase 1 - Coinflip End-to-End)\n- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n- **Phase boundary**: Phase 1 — required to make coinflip functional\n\n## Implementation Context\n\n**Library Choice: Unified Wallet Kit (`@jup-ag/wallet-adapter`)**\n\n- Package: `@jup-ag/wallet-adapter` (built on `@solana/wallet-adapter-react`)\n- Provides: `UnifiedWalletProvider`, `UnifiedWalletButton`, `useUnifiedWallet`\n- Built-in modal UI with dark theme, multi-language, mobile support\n- Auto-detects Wallet Standard wallets (Phantom, Solflare, Backpack) — no manual adapter list needed\n- Wraps Anza's `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` internally → `useWallet()` hook works from either\n- Why not bare adapter: Unified gives us styled modal + button out of box, no custom UI work\n- Why not ConnectorKit: Different API shape (`useConnector`/`useAccount`), would need adapter layer\n\n**Provider Setup Pattern:**\n\n```tsx\n<ConnectionProvider endpoint={rpcUrl}>\n  <UnifiedWalletProvider wallets={[]} config={{\n    autoConnect: true,\n    env: 'devnet',\n    metadata: { name: 'RNG Utopia', ... },\n    theme: 'dark',\n  }}>\n    <App />\n  </UnifiedWalletProvider>\n</ConnectionProvider>\n```\n\n**Key Codebase Findings:**\n\n- `packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx` — currently wraps `MockWalletProvider`, swap target\n- `packages/wallet/src/types.ts` — `WalletContextValue` interface maps 1:1 to adapter's `useWallet`\n- `packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts` — consumers import from here, bridge to adapter\n- `CoinflipContext.tsx:22` — imports `useWallet` from `@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks`\n- `CoinflipContext.tsx:25-26` — reads `VITE_RPC_URL`, defaults to localhost\n- `chain.ts` — all tx builders use `@solana/web3.js`, no adapter dependency (clean separation)\n- `.env.example` has `VITE_SOLANA_RPC_URL` but code reads `VITE_RPC_URL` (mismatch to fix)\n- `apps/platform/package.json` already depends on `@rng-utopia/wallet: workspace:*`\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `packages/wallet/src/` — current MockWalletProvider, useWallet, useBalance, types\n- `packages/wallet/src/mock/MockWalletProvider.tsx` — current mock implementation to preserve\n- `packages/wallet/src/context.ts` — shared WalletContext definition\n- `packages/wallet/src/mock/MockWalletState.ts` — mock state management\n- `apps/platform/src/main.tsx` — entry point wrapping App in MockWalletProvider\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` — transaction builders (already use @solana/web3.js)\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` — calls chain.ts + wallet sendTransaction\n- `apps/platform/src/App.tsx` — wallet icon, balance display, connected state\n- `apps/platform/.env.example` — env var template (has RPC URL mismatch to fix)\n\n## Contract Files\n\n- `packages/wallet/src/types.ts` — WalletContextValue interface (connect, disconnect, sendTransaction, signMessage, publicKey, connected)\n- `packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts` — hook consumers must not change\n- `packages/wallet/src/useBalance.ts` — balance hook consumers must not change\n- `packages/ui/src/WalletButton.tsx` — UI component consuming wallet hook\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: Real Wallet Connection\n\nReplace MockWalletProvider with Unified Wallet Kit (`@jup-ag/wallet-adapter`). The kit wraps `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` and provides a themed modal + connect button out of the box. Pass `wallets: []` to use Wallet Standard auto-detection — no manual adapter instantiation needed.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Player can connect Phantom, Solflare, or Backpack via the existing wallet UI\n- [ ] Player can disconnect and reconnect without page reload\n- [ ] Wallet connection state persists across page navigation (SPA)\n- [ ] The `useWallet()` hook returns the same shape (connected, connecting, address, publicKey, connect, disconnect, sendTransaction, signMessage)\n- [ ] No wallet-adapter UI chrome leaks into the medieval theme (Unified Wallet Kit's `theme: 'dark'` used, styled to match)\n\n### FR-2: Real Balance Display\n\nShow the player's actual on-chain SOL balance instead of a mock value.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Balance displayed matches the connected wallet's on-chain lamport balance\n- [ ] Balance updates after transactions (create match, join, claim, cancel)\n- [ ] Balance polls or subscribes at a reasonable interval (no stale values after 10s)\n- [ ] `useBalance()` hook returns the same shape (balance, formatted, formattedCompact, loading, error, refresh)\n\n### FR-3: Real Transaction Signing\n\nAll coinflip actions must sign and send real transactions via the connected wallet.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Create match builds a transaction via chain.ts and sends it through wallet adapter's sendTransaction\n- [ ] Join match, cancel match, and claim payout work the same way\n- [ ] Transaction confirmation is awaited before updating UI state\n- [ ] Wallet rejection (user clicks \"Cancel\" in Phantom) surfaces a user-friendly error, not a raw exception\n- [ ] RPC errors (insufficient balance, account not found) surface user-friendly messages\n\n### FR-4: RPC Configuration\n\nThe app must connect to a configurable Solana RPC endpoint. Note: `.env.example` currently uses `VITE_SOLANA_RPC_URL` but code reads `VITE_RPC_URL` — this mismatch must be resolved (standardize on `VITE_RPC_URL`). The `ConnectionProvider` from `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` wraps the app, making `useConnection()` available to all components (replacing the per-context `Connection` instantiation in `CoinflipContext`).\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] RPC URL is read from VITE_RPC_URL environment variable\n- [ ] Defaults to devnet when no variable is set\n- [ ] Localhost (test-validator) works when VITE_RPC_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8899\n- [ ] `.env.example` updated to use `VITE_RPC_URL` (fixing mismatch)\n\n### FR-5: TestWalletProvider for CI\n\nA test-only wallet provider that injects a Keypair and signs real transactions without a browser extension.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] TestWalletProvider accepts a Keypair and RPC URL\n- [ ] It implements the same WalletContextValue interface as the real provider\n- [ ] It can sign and send transactions to a local test-validator\n- [ ] MockWalletProvider is preserved for visual-only testing (no chain dependency)\n\n### FR-6: Visual Preservation\n\nThe wallet swap must not alter the site's visual appearance.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Wallet icon in bottom-right corner remains identical\n- [ ] Balance display format unchanged\n- [ ] Connect/disconnect flow uses the same UI elements (no wallet-adapter default modal unless styled)\n- [ ] All non-wallet pages render identically before and after the swap\n- [ ] Visual regression screenshots (spec 200) pass with zero diff on non-wallet elements\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- A player can connect a real wallet, create a coinflip match, and see it on-chain\n- The site looks identical before and after the wallet swap (verified by visual regression)\n- E2E tests can run with TestWalletProvider against a local validator\n- MockWalletProvider still works for visual/component testing (no chain needed)\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Spec 200 (Visual Regression) — baselines must be captured BEFORE this work begins\n- On-chain programs deployed to localnet or devnet\n- `@jup-ag/wallet-adapter` package (Unified Wallet Kit)\n- `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (peer dependency, provided by Unified Wallet Kit)\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- Unified Wallet Kit (`@jup-ag/wallet-adapter`) chosen per team decision\n- Players use standard Solana browser extension wallets (Phantom, Solflare, Backpack)\n- Privy/embedded wallets are deferred to V1.5 (per DECISIONS.md)\n- The `useWallet()` and `useBalance()` hook interfaces are stable and sufficient\n- Dark theme used (`theme: 'dark'`), can be styled further post-V1\n- Wallet Standard auto-detection means no manual adapter instantiation needed\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Phantom connects | Manual test with Phantom extension | Screenshot of connected state |\n| 2 | Balance is real | Compare displayed balance with `solana balance` CLI | Side-by-side screenshot |\n| 3 | Create match works | Create match, verify PDA exists on-chain | Explorer link or `solana account` output |\n| 4 | Visual unchanged | Spec 200 screenshot diff | Zero-diff report on non-wallet elements |\n| 5 | TestWalletProvider works | E2E test with test-validator | Test pass output |\n| 6 | Hook shape preserved | TypeScript compilation | No type errors in consuming code |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n\n#### Pre-existing scaffold (untested — validation required in later iterations)\n- [x] [frontend] `RealWalletProvider.tsx` wrapping `UnifiedWalletProvider` + `ConnectionProvider` + `WalletBridge` mapping adapter hooks to `WalletContextValue` (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n- [x] [frontend] `TestWalletProvider.tsx` accepting `Keypair` + `rpcUrl`, signing real transactions via `sendAndConfirmTransaction` (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n- [x] [frontend] `WalletProvider.tsx` delegates to `MockWalletProvider` or lazy-loaded `RealWalletProvider` based on `VITE_MOCK_MODE` (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n- [x] [frontend] `useBalance.ts` checks `isMock` flag — mock mode reads from `getBalanceLamports()`, real mode polls `connection.getBalance()` every 10s (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n- [x] [frontend] RPG wallet icon in `App.tsx` calls `connect()`/`disconnect()` — `WalletBridge.connect()` opens Unified Wallet modal via `setShowModal(true)` (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n- [x] [frontend] `parseTransactionError()` in `CoinflipContext.tsx` handles: wallet rejection, insufficient funds, network errors, program errors, generic fallback (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n- [x] [frontend] `.env.example` has `VITE_MOCK_MODE`, `VITE_RPC_URL`, `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK` (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n- [x] [frontend] `chain.ts` transaction builders (`buildCreateMatchTx`, `buildJoinMatchTx`, `buildCancelMatchTx`, `buildClaimPayoutTx`) integrated into `CoinflipContext` via `sendTransaction` from `useWallet()` (done: pre-existing scaffold)\n\n#### Iteration 1: Build validation in real wallet mode\n- [x] [frontend] Set `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false`, run `pnpm build` for the platform app — fix any TS compilation errors in `packages/wallet/src/real/`, `packages/wallet/src/test/`, and `packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx`. Run `pnpm lint` (zero errors) and platform `pnpm typecheck` (zero errors). (done: iteration 1)\n\n#### Iteration 2: Shared ConnectionProvider across all wallet modes\n- [x] [frontend] Move `ConnectionProvider` from inside `RealWalletProvider.tsx` to `WalletProvider.tsx` level — wraps both Mock and Real providers. Endpoint: `VITE_RPC_URL` env var, defaults to `https://api.devnet.solana.com`. `RealWalletProvider` drops its own `ConnectionProvider` wrapper and uses the shared one. Verify build + typecheck pass in both mock and real modes. (done: iteration 2)\n\n#### Iteration 3: CoinflipContext + useBalance use shared Connection\n- [x] [frontend] Update `CoinflipContext.tsx` to use `useConnection()` from `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` instead of `new Connection(RPC_URL)` — delete the `RPC_URL` constant and the `useMemo(() => new Connection(...))`. Update `useBalance.ts` to use `useConnection()` instead of its internal `connectionRef` + `getRpcUrl()` — remove the `getConnection` callback, `connectionRef`, and `DEFAULT_RPC_URL` constant. Verify build + typecheck pass. (done: iteration 3)\n\n#### Iteration 4: Mock mode + visual regression preservation\n- [x] [test] Run `pnpm test:visual` — all 17 visual regression baselines pass with zero diff (confirms wallet refactor didn't alter mock mode UI). Start dev server in mock mode (default `VITE_MOCK_MODE` unset), load in Playwright headless, verify zero JS console errors. (done: iteration 4)\n\n#### Iteration 5: Real mode app startup validation\n- [x] [test] Start dev server with `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false` and `VITE_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com`. Load the app in Playwright headless — verify: no JS console errors, wallet icon renders in disconnected state, clicking the wallet icon calls `connect()` without crashing (Unified Wallet modal opens or shows \"no wallets detected\" — both valid in headless). (done: iteration 5)\n\n#### Iteration 6: TestWalletProvider unit test\n- [ ] [test] Write a vitest test in `packages/wallet/src/test/TestWalletProvider.test.tsx`: render a component tree wrapped in `TestWalletProvider({ keypair: Keypair.generate(), rpcUrl: \"https://api.devnet.solana.com\" })`, verify `useWallet()` returns `connected: true` and `publicKey` matching the keypair after mount (use `waitFor`). Also render with `MockWalletProvider` and verify it returns `connected: false` initially. Both tests must pass.\n\n#### Iteration 7: Final verification\n- [ ] [test] Run `pnpm test:visual` — all baselines pass. Run `pnpm lint` and platform `typecheck` — zero errors. Verify app starts in both mock and real modes without console errors. Run `./scripts/verify` — passes (exit 0).\n\n### Testing Requirements\n\nThe agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n\n#### Code Quality\n- [ ] All existing tests pass\n- [ ] No lint errors\n- [ ] TypeScript compiles with no errors\n\n#### Functional Verification\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n- [ ] Wallet connect/disconnect works (validated in Playwright headless — real mode loads, connect() callable)\n- [ ] Transaction building compiles and wallet adapter sendTransaction is callable (TypeScript verification)\n- [ ] Full coinflip lifecycle (create → join → resolve → claim) deferred to 001-coinflip spec (requires VRF oracle)\n\n#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n- [ ] Wallet UI matches existing design (RPG wallet icon preserved)\n- [ ] No wallet-adapter default styling visible on non-wallet pages\n- [ ] Visual regression baselines pass with zero diff in mock mode\n\n#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n- [ ] No JS console errors in mock mode\n- [ ] No JS console errors in real mode (connected to devnet)\n- [ ] No failed RPC requests when connected to valid endpoint\n\n### Iteration Instructions\n\nIf ANY check fails:\n1. Identify the specific issue\n2. Fix the code\n3. Re-run tests\n4. Re-verify all criteria\n5. Check again\n\n**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n\n### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n\nAfter the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n","numLines":278,"startLine":1,"totalLines":278}}}
