{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UbYiRvNFziqyN7EYbJW3Kg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No `@testing-library/react` in the repo. The `TestWalletProvider` makes network calls in `connect()` (`connection.getBalance`), which makes it tricky for unit tests. Let me think about the approach.\n\nThe spec says: \"render a component tree wrapped in `TestWalletProvider({ keypair: Keypair.generate(), rpcUrl: \"https://api.devnet.solana.com\" })`, verify `useWallet()` returns `connected: true` and `publicKey` matching the keypair after mount\".\n\nThe `TestWalletProvider` auto-connects on mount and calls `connection.getBalance()` in its `connect()` method. For a vitest unit test, we need to either:\n1. Mock the `Connection.getBalance` call\n2. Use `@testing-library/react` for rendering React components\n\nSince `@testing-library/react` isn't installed and we need React rendering, I need to install the necessary test dependencies. Let me also check what the `WalletProvider.tsx` wrapping looks like, and whether `ConnectionProvider` is involved."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":854,"cache_read_input_tokens":51658,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":854},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e148c6ae-d46e-4f5a-b974-9f3c7b2cbc1a","uuid":"23def4c4-984c-4d6c-a42d-6a976c3b2044"}
